{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:42:01.463Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Objective**\n\nI'm now clarifying the immediate objective. It involves constructing a premium view for project and program management located at `/portal/projects`, distinct from the landing page. It needs to include a project display such as cards or a table with search and filtering capabilities for status and phase.\n\n\n**Refining the UI**\n\nI'm now iterating on the UI components for `/portal/projects`, envisioning a high-end enterprise delivery dashboard feel. Specifically, I'm integrating project cards or a table with key search and filtering functionality. I'm focusing on fields like Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, owner, timeline, progress, next milestone, and health status. Preview data is planned for the display. The local detail drawer will be integrated, and I will be sure to add a CTA (call to action) to request updates. I am considering a card view for mobile devices.\n\n\n**Integrating Detail Views**\n\nI'm now focusing on the project detail view integration for `/portal/projects/[id]/page.tsx`, deciding between a premium local drawer and full page view. I'm leaning toward *both* - a contained detail drawer *within* the dashboard, and an option to expand to a full page. I'm also ensuring a frontend-only CTA for updates or support requests. Mobile card views are a priority, and I need to run lint and build. I'm thinking of this as part of a \"GFF AI Sovereign Projects Deck\" design.\n\n\n**Envisioning the Interface**\n\nI am now visualizing the portal interface for enterprise generative AI deployments. I see a dark mode control deck, terminal-inspired yet elegant, with sections mirroring radar readouts for Garage, Foundry, Factory, and Operate phases. This deck provides traceability across project phases, incorporating live health metrics, milestones, and timelines. I'm focusing on high contrast, neon accents, and clean SVG indicators to create an intuitive but powerful visual experience.\n\n\n**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI'm now focusing on the dashboard layout. I want a clean interface with a prominent search bar, status and phase filters, and an easy reset. For the main content, I'm leaning toward a premium, responsive grid of cards, transitioning to a list view or an interactive grid. Each card will showcase key project information with a \"View Details\" button to open a slide-over drawer. The mobile view is designed for touch-friendly cards.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactions**\n\nI'm now implementing the interaction strategy for the project dashboard. Specifically, I am focusing on real-time search filters and phase selection for usability. I'm prioritizing smooth hover micro-interactions on the project cards, like border highlights, gradient tracking, and scaling arrow icons, for improved visual appeal. I'm also implementing a click-to-open slide-over drawer with a seamless transition, and a \"Request Update\" button with a sleek interactive form. I'm planning to use state transitions and CSS animations for a performant and robust user experience.\n\n\n"}}
