{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:42:26.027Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Imports and Features**\n\nI've discovered the `motion` library is imported from `\"motion/react\"`. I'm now exploring the `/portal/projects/page.tsx` file, aiming to identify features that can be enhanced for a premium user experience while ensuring complete compliance with established guardrails. I'm focusing on the `/portal/projects` prompt and its requirements.\n\n\n**Designing Mock Project Data**\n\nI'm now structuring representative preview data. I'm focusing on crafting a high-end enterprise delivery dashboard aesthetic. I'm building a mockup dataset of 5-6 projects. Each has a realistic name, diverse phases like Garage, Foundry, Factory, and Operate, along with owners, timelines, progress metrics, upcoming milestones, and health statuses. This frontend-only data includes \"Sovereign Audit & Compliance Ledger\". I'm aiming for both mobile card views and detailed views.\n\n\n**Detailing Project Attributes**\n\nI'm now detailing project specifications. I've documented \"PROJ-202: Sovereign Audit & Compliance Ledger\", including Evelyn Chen's 18% progress, and Marcus Aurelius' \"Apex RetailMesh Agent Lattice\" at 48%. These projects highlight diverse owners, phases, progress, and crucial milestones to enhance premium user interaction.\n\n\n**Expanding Project Details**\n\nI've documented additional project details. I've added \"PROJ-302: Sovereign Defense Risk Parser\", owned by Dr. Sarah Vance, currently at 74% progress in the \"Factory\" phase, with a \"Warning\" health status and the \"Sovereign Air-Gap Decoupling Test\" milestone. Then, I added \"PROJ-209: TelecomVerse Network Self-Healer\", owned by Devon Carter, at 100% progress in the \"Operate\" phase with an \"On Track\" health status and the \"Automated Routine Guardrail Audit\" milestone.\n\n\n**Adding Project Details**\n\nI've documented two more projects. \"PROJ-105: OreMesh Sub-Surface Vision Grid\" is at 35% progress, owned by Elena Rostova, with a Critical health status and requiring remediation. Then, \"PROJ-882: EnergyVerse Multi-Grid Balance Agent\", owned by Tariq Al-Mansoor, has 8% progress and is On Track.\n\n\n**Defining Page Layout**\n\nI'm now focusing on the page layout, specifically `/portal/projects/page.tsx`. I'm designing a header block with summary cards. This will consist of four carefully designed metric cards, organized in a custom dashboard grid. I'll include Active Engagements, System Lifecycle, Resource Utilization, and Overall Program Health metrics for display.\n\n\n**Refining Card Design**\n\nI'm now refining the summary card details. I'm focusing on premium SVG icons, clean borders, custom gradients, and glowing effects. The layout will avoid box-inside-box clutter.\n\nI'm starting to build a filter and search bar, elegantly designed for a dark theme. It will have a search bar with a \"Search by ID, project name, or owner...\" placeholder using a Lucide search icon. It'll also include select dropdowns for Lifecycle Phase (All Phases, Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate) and Health Status (All Statuses, On Track, Warning/At Risk, Critical), along with a quick reset button.\nIn the desktop view, I'm thinking of incorporating a Grid of cards or a Table view, along with a View Toggle (Grid vs. List/Table). The default view will be a modern responsive Grid of cards.\n\n\n**Designing Card Elements**\n\nI'm now detailing card content, specifically \"Sovereign Audit & Compliance Ledger\". I'm implementing a health status badge with color coding, and crafting the card body, with title, owner, description, and lifecycle phase stepper with a crisp progress bar. I am particularly proud of the linear stepper. The footer will show the next milestone. I'm focusing on \"View Telemetry & Spec\" functionality to open a premium detail drawer.\n\n\n\n**Constructing the Detail Drawer**\n\nI'm now implementing the slide-over